column4: A Gigas born under the influence of 'Steel' and 'Order'. The will of Hooul the Creator is manifested most strongly in this Gigas, reflecting the wish of the god who wanted a giant of steel that will restore order. It was the first one to be born from a Fr

Gigas, born by the affects of 'earth' and 'protection'. Differ from the others, its appearance has changed due to the form of earth. Born sixth from fruit of giant and has powerful defense ability to protect the others.

A Gigas created by the influence of 'Rock' and 'Will'. It was born the third from the Fruit of Giant. As it has mighty power and body optimized for spreading its will further, it is suitable for battles in a wider field.

Gigas, born by the affects of 'Insect' and 'tenacity'. Born fourth from the fruit of giant and inherited negativity, a bit snaky and tenacious. Like his character, he persistly seek the enemy and sometimes use poison.
Gigas, born by the affects of 'tree' and 'peace'. Born second from fruit of giant, a bit weak compare to the others but has an mysterious ability to heal them.
A Gigas born under the influence of 'Bat' and 'Darkness'. Born fifth from a Fruit of Giant, it drives enemies into darkness and confuses them.

A Gigas born under the influence of 'Steel' and 'Order'. The will of Hooul the Creator is manifested most strongly in this Gigas, reflecting the wish of the god who wanted a giant of steel that will restore order. It was the first one to be born from a Fr

Gigas, born by the affects of 'earth' and 'protection'. Differ from the others, its appearance has changed due to the form of earth. Born sixth from fruit of giant and has powerful defense ability to protect the others.

A Gigas created by the influence of 'Rock' and 'Will'. It was born the third from the Fruit of Giant. As it has mighty power and body optimized for spreading its will further, it is suitable for battles in a wider field.

Gigas, born by the affects of 'Insect' and 'tenacity'. Born fourth from the fruit of giant and inherited negativity, a bit snaky and tenacious. Like his character, he persistly seek the enemy and sometimes use poison.
A Gigas born under the influence of 'Tree' and 'Peace'. Born second from a Fruit of Giant, it is weaker in strength than other Gigases but has a mysterious power to heal and protect them.
A Gigas born under the influence of 'Bat' and 'Darkness'. Born fifth from a Fruit of Giant, it drives enemies into darkness and confuses them.

Gigas, born by the affects of 'bird' and 'heal'. Differ from the others whom born from fruit of startree, he was born of his own will from incomplete fruit of startree. He's smaller and more active comparing to the others.

Gigas, born by the affects of 'Time' and 'Perseverance'. Minor gigas like Igzalto, created from incomplete fruit of startree and the piece of spirit which Alex Rose left in his watch for Sherill Rose. Like Igzalto, it can be acquired fully by being stabilized through 'Leaf of Startree'.

column3: To summon a Gigas, first press the hotkey "N" and add the Gigas icon to an empty slot on your Hot Key Bar.
You can acquire a Gigas by completing Gigas themed Quests at Level 28. For more information, visit our homepage.
You can increase the power of a Gigas by mounting a Resonant Stone on the Gigas.
You can move freely from region to region by using a Celero Station. To use a Celero Station, first you need to activate the Celero Station in the region where you are.
You can take a Sigil item to a Blacksmith and attempt to make a Sphere Setting on  your weapons or armor. Whether you succeed in making a Sphere Setting or not, the Sigil will be consumed.
You can easily buy and sell items in the Auction House.
Before you use the Gate Keeper's Feather, you need to ask a Gatekeeper to remember the position. If you lose it, you can get another one from the Gatekeeper.
Each city has an NPC with a  [Guild] mark who enbles you to create a guild. To create a guild, you must be Level 5 or higher and purchase a "Unity Stone."
You can buy or sell goods through the Auctineer NPC in each village and city.
If you have serious lag problems, pressing CTRL+Z to play in the Shadow mode can enhance your gaming experience.
Lon Mas must be Level 10 or higher and have completed the quest "Message from the Room of Rest" to meet Anima.
Lon Femina must be Level 10 or higher and have completed the quest "My Keepsake..." to meet Anima.
If a monster has a white name, it is a Passive Monster and will only respond when engaged first. If it has a red name, it is an Aggressive monster and will actively engage players.
You can see the Quest Navigation on the Mini Map and World Map. You can select quests to be displayed on this Navigation by using Quest Shortcut and Quest List (U).
Beriah must be Level 10 or higher and have completed the quest "Nostalgic Song" to meet Anima.
When your inventory is full, you can keep unnecessary items in your Atrium Storage.
The hotkey to take screenshots is the"Print Screen" key. Screenshots will be saved in ...>Programs Files(x86)>Prius Online>ScreenShots folder.
You can earn the Skill Points required to learn and improve skills by leveling up.
You can easily swap weapons by clicking Skill View (K) > Action > Change Weapons icon and placing it on your Hot Key Bar or by pressing the R hotkey.
You can earn a Pero by completing the Soothe Anima quests. You must be Level 20 or higher to do the Soothe Anima quests.
The hotkey to swap between Anima mode and your character is F11. Some NPCs can only be seen or offer quest when you are in Anima Mode.
You can get Anima Clothes by buying clothes from Anima Merchants or by hunting Bestias.
You can resurrect a dead Anima by moving to the Atrium or by using the Anima Resurrection Potion. The Adventor's Campfire can also resurrect a dead Anima.
Anima's disposition varies depending on its in-game actions and decides its personality and skills.
You must be Level 10 or higher and complete the relevant quest to meet Anima. For more information, visit our homepage.
Press the Z key to pick Up Items, X key to Sit, Insert key to Auto Run, and the Tab key to cycle through Targetable Monsters.
You can equip, destroy, or offer an item as a present to Anima by right clicking the items icon and selecting the option.
Ayins must be Level 10 or higher and have completed the quest "What Came from the Room of Rest" to meet Anima.
You can check the quests you have completed in the Quest Memorial within the Atrium.
You can receive Cultivation, Gathering, Requiem, Soothe, and Cooking quests from Cepa the Gardner whom you can see only in Anima mode in the Atrium.
If you want to go to the Atrium or a village of other races, use the [Terasil Gate] in each village.
Enter /Y to Yell, /w + ID info to whisper, /G to talk to guild, /P to talk to party, and /S to speak normally.
You can exchange letters with other Adventurers by using the Mail button in the bottom right of the screen.
Some common hotkeys are: M for World Map, B for Inventory, U for Quest View, Z for Pick Up Item, P for Party View, and [ for Friends View.
You can Cultivate to produce items that may be helpful in playing the game.
If you find your character spinning in place after you log in, pressing A, Z, space bar or  ??ey should resolve the issue.
Some common hotkeys are: C for Character Info, V for Anima Info, N for Gigas Info, and L for Anima's Knowledge View.
The Quest Storybook (U) helps you keep track of how your main quests (Anima, Gigas, or Dungeon) are developing.
You can move your character by pressing the W, A, S, and D keys on the keyboard, or by enabling Mouse Control in the Game Options, game tab, and left-clicking the point you would like to move to.
If you find an error, for example, the character being stuck in a specific terrain, please report it to 1:1 Service > Bug (Error) > Character Isolation category.
Select the Convert to Expedition menu in the Party Info View to form an expedition with up to 18 members.
Humes must be Level 10 or higher and have completed the quest "Something Left Behind" to meet Anima.
If you hide the UI by pressing ALT + Z  you can take better screenshots.
The red exclamation point above an NPC indicates that the NPC has a quest available. These NPCs will also be marked as exclamation points on the Mini Map.
You can mine by using the Auto Mine menu. If you have a Drill, just click the Auto Mine icon.
How about doing your own cooking? You can make high quality food from materials dropped by Bestias.
You can decorate the Atrium as you please by buy Interior items from Atrium Merchants in the big cities.
Don't forget to check your mail box, you will often get mail when your level goes up that may contain new quest and rewards!
Press and hold both mouse buttons and you can move the character in the direction it is facing
You can challenge for the Phantasm Dungeon through the Terasill Gate in the village. Make a party and challenge for the Phantasm Dungeon.
To use a Cerelo, you first need to activate the Celero Station. Whenever you find a new Celero Station, be sure to activate it.
To participate in the Coliseum, use the [Festival] option in the main menu or talk to the Coliseum Manager of each village.
You can register a player as a friend or block him or her in the [Community] tab of the main menu. You can have a 1:1 Chat with a player registered as a friend.
If you're level 35 or higher, you can begin the  "Gigas - Song of Birds" Quest that rewards you with Gigas Igzalto.
You can create a chat room by selecting Main Menu > [Community] > Find a Chat Room.
You can move to other channels by selecting Main Menu > [Option] > Change Channel.
Each village has a Blacksmith NPC who can Craft or Dismantle items for you.
If you sell an item to a shop by mistake, you can buy up to 12 items back from the shops Buy Back tab.

It is rumored to have been formed by the Maneating Flowers or the Carnivore Flowers that have eaten the fairies. ...but we'll never know the truth.
Only the highest quality crystal grapes are used for making the Crystal Wine. Crisp clean taste makes you feel like you're in a new world with a vivid image of crystal shining before your eyes.
Healthy apple nurtured with abundant ray of sunlight. Over 80% of the cultivation of this fruit is contributed by the sun!
Soft and sweet mango that grows on a tree that shoots up above the clouds. But because it's so high up, only those with wings can pick these fruits.
"This is the true taste of heaven! This Kiwi was sent by the gods to make heavenly wine!" - Hume sommelier
Refreshing, sweet and highly nutritious orange. Only those that can peel off the armor like outer skin will be rewarded with the delicious taste of the orange.
The onion that is as sweet as a candy. But that doesn't mean that it's not hot.
Soul tasting lemon that will stir up a tornado in your mouth. But the Flame Souls love this violent taste.
Hot cherries favored by the Flame Lizards. It can only be consumed in a form of juice.
It's a specialty of the snow fields meticulously cultivated by the Snowmen.
Very bountiful fruit that grows to become tasty milk tree when planted. Of course, the fruit can be used for cooking as well.
These plum became highly valued ever since it was rumored to increase stamina
Precious pear known to drop like a shooting star when fully ripe
Gloomy cucumber that feeds on heavy floods
The king of the chrysanthemums. There is not a bigger or more extravagant chrysanthemum.
Symbol of happiness It's known to provide the energy of happiness when carried around.
A leaf of Laurel. It has a unique scent.
Cool and sweet cactus sap that's refreshing to drink as is. It also possess various vitamins and minerals.
The flower petal for making the Whole Flower Liquor. It's got a wonderful scent.
The ultimate green tea leaf with golden shine. The Outrageous Minerbot often mistakes the Golden Green Leaf for real gold.
Cool and refreshing scent of pine needles. It is known to restore your energy if drank as tea.
If you slice the antler of a female deer, honey like sap will come out. That's Deer Antler Licorice!

column4: It's a hardened block of Auromatic Milk Tree Sap. This baking ingredient is definitely needed.
Mysterious plant nurtured with spirits' care
Strong aloe that has grown healthy for many years
Even the Bestias know that the Magia Plant is good for your body.
A fruit of the Thunder Pear Tree known to bear fruit only on the days of thunder.
The flour is used for baking rye bread.
Cream filling for Sweet Cream Bun. Cream roll without cream filling just isn't a cream roll.
Spice mixed with various herbs and accents. But don't rely on this too much.
It's an essential ingredient for frying.
It's an essential ingredient for making liquor.
It's dried yeast to add convenience when baking bread.
It's the basic and the finale for cooking. A true chef is the one who can well balance the use of salt.
The source of sweet taste that makes people happy. Life would have been more gloomy without sugar in this world.
Unique flavored pepper. Used both independently and as a component of All-Purpose Spice.
Ultimate fiery essence extracted from the souls of the Flame Soul. Drop of this into any dish is a murderous act.
Clean and natural ingredient from the Mistwood. Used as the main ingredient for the Mistwood Dew Liquor
Lava stone that still possess heat from the volcano. Place this into an alcohol to make Lava Liquor that will heat up your body.
Elaborately colored sweet candy. You can eat the candy as is but it's mostly used as a decorative item on baked goods.
Used to make chocolates for Valentine Day. It can also be consumed by mixing it in water with syrup.
It's an ingredient for making Sunny Apple Candy. Sometimes, it turns the recipe into an Angel's Candy.
Gorgeous Candy Basket. It's definitely overdone package. It's the thought that counts, isn't it.
A legendary seasoning that passes down the taste of good old grandma's cooking. Single Use Recipe:  Grandma's Songpyeon Ingredient
Made of fine powders of newly harvested rice.

Quality bone-in Meat fun for gnawing.

Sweet-flavored liquor which is widely known as the liquor for seamen. Even Muscle Pirates like it very much.
Lemon with rich vitamin C. It is used in Bing Bing Drink Recipe.
Body-friendly ion crystal that facilitates the absorption of every intake.
Mint liquid good for relieving fatigue.
Raisin Tree Fruit known to be good for liver.
Nutrition enhancer full of all kinds of nutriment.
One of the three fruits for those who work at night alongside Overworky Fruit and Me Fatigue Fruit.

This item enables you to Warp instantly to a pre-registered Region on the Travel Menu.
Simply activate Star Gate, select the [Region] tab and find your desired destination.
Once you have found the correct destination, press the [Travel] button. 
Successfully Warping to a players location will consume 1 Star Step.

This item enables you to Warp instantly to a Saved Location you have created on the Travel Menu.
Simply activate Star Feather, select the [Saved] tab and find your desired destination.
Once you have found the correct destination, press the [Travel] button. 
Successfully Warping to a players location will consume 1 Star Feather.

This item enables you to Warp instantly to the location of any Player.
Simply activate Star Warp, select the [Search] tab enter a character's name.
Once you have found the correct character, press the [Travel] button. 
Successfully Warping to a players location will consume 1 Star Warp.

This item enables you to instantly Summon any Player to your location if the accept.
Simply activate Star Summon, select the [Search] tab enter a character's name.
Once you have found the correct character, press the [Summon] button. 
Successfully Summoning a player will consume 1 Star Summon.

Press ~ (Shift+`) on the keyboard to view basic control tips.
Playing the game for a prolonged period could harm your health.
Press the Insert key to make your character run forward.
Click both left and right mouse buttons simultaneously to make your character run forward.
Press Alt+R to switch between Run/Walk.
Opening the map while a quest is selected from the quest list displays the target area for the quest.
Press V to open the Anima info window.
After obtaining a quest talk to the NPC again to obtain additional information about the quest.
Press U to view the list of quests currently in progress. You can select a quest from the list to create a shortcut.
Opening the map while a quest is selected from the quest list displays the target area for the quest.
The Mini-map displays the direction to the target area for the selected quest.
Press T to approach and talk to the nearest NPC.
Press Z near an item to pick it up automatically. You can't pick up items that you have no right to.
When the game slows down because there are many other players nearby you could press CTRL+Z to turn off the display of other players. (On/Off)
You cannot mount a Pero or consume food while you are engaging in a battle.
During a battle you gain threat level when using direct healing skills or inflicting damage. Most of Bestias attack the target who has the highest threat level.
Defender Gladiator and Dark Holy Knight are tanker class. They have higher defense ability than other classes
Magiablade Striker and Shadow Knight are melee dealer class. They can inflict a great damage on enemies.
Sniper and Strider are ranged dealer class. They can inflict a great damage on enemies from long distance.
Warlock and Dancer are Magia dealer class. They have powerful attack skills but have a weakness in their defense.
Scholar and Rapidshooter are hybrid class. They have various skills that complement their party's weak points.
Prayer and Shaman are healer class. They can recover HP and remove debuffs.
The effect of healing skills increases based on the healing amount and the additional healing amount are added to the result to increase the recovery amount.
The effect of attack skill increases based on each attack power. The Final attack power is added to result value and increases damage.
Debuffs are grouped into Poison Wound
Elemental resistances are effective in reducing damage sustained. Most of Magia attacks have an attribute and cannot be deflected entirely with Magia resistance.
You can get points by defeating other players.
While the arena is in progress, moving to a different place resets the points earned in the arena.
Capture bases in the arena to get more scores.
You can gain victory by capturing over half the bases present and defend successfully for a set period of time.
Protect your flag from the enemy, and capture their flag and bring it back to your base to earn points.
While the arena is in progress, moving to a different place resets the points earned in the arena.
You can gain victory by occupying the throne in the center of the arena for a set period of time.
While the arena is in progress, moving to a different place resets the points earned in the arena.
Debuff with no attribute cannot be lifted from a player manually.
Majority of Boss Bestia are immune to silence, stun, and freeze.

Once Chaotic Joke is in effect, getting close to Chaos Executioner can minimize damage you receive.
When Red Wavelength is in effect, attacking Annihilation Beast can be extremely dangerous!
Using randomly summoned tool, run away from boss bestia.
All party members need to receive the Breath of Flame, except those already with Burn.
We must go on before the enemies swarm us!
That side needs assistance! We must hurry!
Be careful! The enemies are approaching!
We will fight Valak, the rest is up to you!
Pzz.... Pzzst.... I'm Patriarch Yorupa.... ... Pzz....
Solutus's.... Altar...probably broken.... ... if you .... hear me...
spray Spore Powder... on the altar... Spore Powder... 10 spores of Shamanfungus... gather... use...
Sniff. Ah, thank God! I think we're connected now, Yorupa!
I think someone sprayed Spore Powder on the Altar of Communication! Thank you! Can you hear me?
It's me! Pilgrim Sopona! I'm here! Please grab Bibie for me!
Psh~ I can't hear very well. I guess it's not completely fixed.
I will send someone to Solutus to fix the Altar of Communication. Please hold on until then.
Oops, Financier I am sorry. I'll be right there!
You're still clumsy. You haven't changed at all. *chuckle*
I suppose she finally achieved her dream of becoming an Aide while I was traveling around.
Put the Crystal of Magia Power in this Magia Pattern Analyzer...
Done! Let's wait for the results of the Analyzer.
Hm. Just as I thought. It has been affected by the Elemental Basilis and now it is showing mutated patterns.
....What! The Analyzer is going out of control!
Oh no, the machine is completely broken.
How dare you try to ruin Prophet Boowoo's plans! Insolent fools!!
The tried to destroy my Dark Crystal? I'll make them pay for this! Boowoo!
Boowooo!!! How could I lose to these imbeciles.... upsetting, Boowoo...
You could talk the talk, but, you couldn't walk the walk.
I, Valak, will gratefully take the power that you have collected in the Dark Crystal!
Hey you, the one who defeated Boowoo. I'm sorry, but you'll have to die here.
I'm sure this wouldn't happen, but if you interfere... Hm? You are!
You should have died in the Lava Cave of Insanity!
Anima.... That must be it! Did you come back as a Xenor?  How persistent.
I will honor your iron will and generously let you go today.
No matter how many times you come back, you cannot defeat me!
I look forward to your outstanding performance!
The chosen one. lead the people with me!
.... (Legnatt emphasize how we have been chosen a bit too much)
(The rumors about his political moves to be the next Prime Minister might be true...)
I don't know who you are, but I'm in your debt! I would've died if it weren't for you!!
Shoot! It's way past the time I promised to return. I must hurry!
You should leave right now as well, instead of lingering in a dangerous place like this!
Every time General Borek absorbs slime, he gets stronger.
Convicting Female Priest uses more spells as her HP goes down. Be careful of ground skills!
Chaos Executioner is creating chaotic mischief. Get close to Chaos Executioner!
Chaos Executioner is using DOT Earthquake. Get out of the way!
If you successfully lure Chaos Executioner into the Pillar of Light, urge of destruction can be eliminated.
Incomplete Igniseer is creating Lava Breath.
Only max leveled character may enter Hero's Shadowless Dungeon.
You must have Invitation for Masquerade
Aah! There's someone there! I think we got caught! We're in trouble!
Run now! Let's split up in different directions!
Here, I'll approve it. Go get it verified with Legnatt.
Delegate Rugaba! This is difference of two digits! How are these amounts at all similar? Every Lon Mas has such terrible financial intelligence! Don't you understand?! This pre-set budget
is the most Solutus Union Council can pay. I understand that Fungus Forest agenda is important, but the Union Council has many other places to spend money!
We're already financially troubled and you do something like this? Look, if you think a little in for these items, you can lower the spending...
What is it! I still have much to say!
That's enough! I will let Delegate Emmerson handle all budget related issues.
My head will explode if I have to listen to you any longer.
Tsk, tsk. You lack patience. I know about Fungus Forest Investigators
So I will take care of it. I will take this budget plan.
That pendant... is the same as the one given to me by the Lon Femina who gave birth to me...?
It was made by my mother, and only my sisters have one...
Doesn't it have the name 'Niame' inscribed on the back?
!! Yes... this pendant has 'Niame' inscribed on it as well!
What the heck are you doing!!!!!!!! You primitive Lon Mas!!
I retaliated by accident...! Excuse me, are you okay? Vodu? Wake up!
You've grown strong. Your big brother... is happy!
Still, come and visit me if you ever need help. Farewell....Cough!
Grr~ Go away! That box is mine!
Will you enchant this totem with the power of purification?
Ban Stone... reflected the power of purification!
One of my men who snuck into Temple of Sun God

This value shows the <info>Base Damage<default> that you inflict on a target when you attack with a <info>Melee Weapon<default>.  This value is determined by your <info>STR<default> and your <info>Level<default> .  This value, in addition to your weapons <info>Attack Power<default> and any other <info>STR Bonuses<default> determines the damage you will inflict.

This value shows the <info>Base Damage<default> that you inflict on a target when you attack with a <info>Ranged Weapon<default>.  This value is determined by your <info>DEX<default> and your <info>Level<default> .  This value, in addition to your weapons <info>Attack Power<default> and any other <info>DEX Bonuses<default> determines the damage you will inflict.

This value shows the <info>Base Damage<default> that you inflict on a target when you attack with a <info>Magia Weapon<default>.  This value is determined by your <info>INT<default> and your <info>Level<default> .  This value, in addition to your weapons <info>Attack Power<default> and any other <info>INT Bonuses<default> determines the damage you will inflict.

This value indicates the amount of damage you negate from a <info>Melee<default> or <info>Ranged Attack<default>.  The default value is determined by your <info>Base HP<default> and your <info>Level<default>.  This value will continue to increase in proportion to your <info>STA<default> and the <info>Defense<default> of your equipment.

This values determines the chance you have of successfully landing an attack on an enemy; the higher the value, the greater the chance of success. The base value is determined by your <info>DEX<default>, <info>Sense<default>, and <info>Luck<default>.  This Value will continue to increase in proportion to any <info>Sense Bonuses<default> you receive.

The value is a bonus percentage applied to your <info>Critical Chance<default>. For every <info>Level<default> you gain, your <Info>Critical Point<default> value will increase by <info>1%<default>.  This value will also increase in proportion to any <info>Luck Bonuses<default> you receive.
This value determines the odds you have of landing a <info>Critical Strike<default> on an opponent.  This value is directly impacted by your <info>CRIT Point<default>.

This value is a bonus percentage applied to your accuracy with <info>Melee Attacks<default>.  This value will only be applied to your <info>Melee Attacks<default> as long as it does not exceed <info>99%<default>.

This value is a bonus percentage applied to your accuracy with <info>Ranged Attacks<default>.  This value will only be applied to your <info>Ranged Attacks<default> as long as it does not exceed <info>99%<default>.

This value is a bonus percentage applied to your accuracy with <info>Magia Attacks<default>.  This value will only be applied to your <info>Magia Attacks<default> as long as it does not exceed <info>99%<default>.

This value indicates the amount of damage you negate from a <info>Magia Attack<default>. The default value is determined by your <info>Base INT<default> and your <info>Level<default>.  This Value will continue to increase in proportion to your <info>Sense<default> and the <info>Magia Resistance<default> of your equipment.

This value determines the chance you have of evading an enemy's attack; the higher the value, the greater the chance you have of evading an incoming attack.  The default value is determined by your <info>DEX<default>, <info>Sense<default>, and <info>Luck<default>.  The value goes up in proportion to any <info>Sense Bonuses<default> you receive.

This value indicates the chance you have of gaining additional defense against <info>Melee<default> or <info>Ranged Attacks<default>; the higher the value, the greater the chance you have of gaining additional defense.  The default value is determined by your <info>Defense<default> and <info>Luck<default>.
In addition, you have a better chance to gain this bonus if your <info>Level<default> is higher then that of your opponent.

This value indicates the percentage of damage you negate from other <info>Player's<default> attacks. 
This percentage will apply up to <info>50%<default>.
This value indicates the <info>Movement Speed<default> of your Character.  The Default value is 100.
You will automatically recover this amount of <info>HP<default> every 5 seconds.
You will automatically recover this amount of <info>MP<default> every 5 seconds.
This value indicates the entire <info>Healing Bonus<default> that you are currently receiving from your equipment.  This bonus is factored into every skill that has a healing effect.
This value indicates the <info>Casting Speed<default> of your Character.  The Default value is 100.
This value indicates the <info>Attack Speed<default> of your Character.  The Default value is 100.
This value indicates the <info>Damage Bonus<default> your character is receiving from their equipment.  It affects the damage of every attack.
This value indicates the amount of damage you negate from a direct <info>Fire Attack<default>.  This value does not impact <info>Debuffs<default> or <info>Periodic Damage<default>.
This value indicates the amount of damage you negate from a direct <info>Water Attack<default>.  This value does not impact <info>Debuffs<default> or <info>Periodic Damage<default>.
This value indicates the amount of damage you negate from a direct <info>Earth Attack<default>.  This value does not impact <info>Debuffs<default> or <info>Periodic Damage<default>.
This value indicates the amount of damage you negate from a direct <info>Wind Attack<default>.  This value does not impact <info>Debuffs<default> or <info>Periodic Damage<default>.
This value indicates the amount of damage you negate from a direct <info>Soul Attack<default>.  This value does not impact <info>Debuffs<default> or <info>Periodic Damage<default>.

When using any skill that recovers <info>HP<default>, this value is used to determine the strength of that skill.  The higher the value, the stronger the effect.  The value is based off of your <info>INT<default> and your <info>Level<default>.

column5: Gigas technology gave birth to Celero.
Lanna is a very picky eater. Also Lanna might seem to be clever and tricky, but she is loved by all adventors because her real personality is very lovely.

Ensis seems ferocious on the outside, but he is more gentle bestia than a unicorn. Ensis is well known to be a gentle bestia to both enemies and allies, but he is also well known to kill his prey instantly to minimize their pain. Unlike other felines, Ensis does not play around with his prey.

Perfero was the first tamed bestia by the adventors. So he goes way back. The term 'pero' is known to originate from Perfero. Perfero possesses soft and kind heart that gets favored by many adventors. Some adventors call him 'pink pig' or 'kid's pero,' but Perfero never loses his smile and keeps running hard for Xenor and Anima.

Larua who seems like she has a mask on is known to be just an ordinary fox. However, according to the rumor, foul magia energy bound the mask to her face. Since she used to be an ordinary fox with many loveable attributes, she regains her personality once tamed.

Even though Jubata is indeed a ferocious bestia, he will become a pero because he will obey to an adventor stronger than him. But if an adventor shows any sigh of weakness, he will take his chance and run away. Because Jubata is fast and costs very little to maintain, he is very popular among the adventors
Porci has a very laid back personality. He likes to eat things that come out from the ground, which is precisely why he is always looking at the ground. Porci hates playing around with food.

Aufero is a carnivorous bird who is very ferocious and stubborn. He is very capable to travel long distance very fast, but he does not like doing favors for Xenor. When he encounters something he does not like, he will not hesitate to use his claws. But once tamed, he never betrays his master.

Cerva is a fantasy pero with beautiful wings and appearance, which gets a lot of attention from adventors. Because of her beautiful appearance, even Regnus adventists would tame her as their pero. Once she is tamed, she will obey her master with no hesitation.

Armentum might look like a carnivore, but he enjoys veggies and peave more than anything . But since plants do not grow well and too many ferocious bestias live in Bestia Inferno, he had no choice but to protect himself with his long horns and scary appearance.
Special edition of Celero technology which originated from Gigas technology. It might look faster because it is red, but its speed is exactly same as ordinary celero.

Silva Pellis who loves to look nice is actually from a cold region of Prius. Silva Pellis is very curious bestia and its coat is so unique that it can shakes off all the ice from its coat with one shake. He is known to be very adept with its paw (some rumors say he can pierce its own ear). Even though Silva looks very friendly and nice, he is especially ferocious in battle.

Karabi has a unique look with its large body and horn, so many adventors make wrong assumption about Karabi. But he is actually a very peaceful bestia who gets along especially with Anima. Many adventors think that he looks gross by the way he walks, but he is also very popular to even have a backpack after him. He is especially popular among race manias.

Bicolen displays unique and noble looks that no peros can match. She was loved by Ayin in the past for her exquisite looks. Unlike some peros that refuse to move when hungry, Bicolen honors her master more than anything. She is a bestia that detests weakness, but she actually loves to eat plants.
Special edition of Celero technology which originated from Gigas technology. It has unique black looks, but its value dropped because it became too common now.
Special edition of Celero technology which originated from Gigas technology. It has luxurious golden looks that adventors cannot resist.

This black lion is known to be the king of all peros. Also he is rumored to be the father of Jubata. Another rumor says scar on his eye was from the battle against Regnus Adventists. He is told to have become very ferocious because he lost his son during the battle. There are many rumors about Leogiti, but one thing for sure is that he can be trusted no matter what.

Moa is loved by many female adventors for her unique way of walking and exceptionally cool personality. Due to her unique personality, she never gets in trouble with adventors. But when she encounters an enemy, she will not hesitate to use her bodyslam and front kick.

Marino is an amphibious pero who is also very friendly to adventors. He likes exploring new areas and is known to be very curious. Even though he sometimes gets too curious, he is nonetheless very good to keep in company.

Draka is known to be the descendent of dragons, so there is no question about how he looks. Rumor says some Eastern country tried creating new type of pero by breeding between a dragon and some different bestia, which resulted Draka to have unique looks.

Silva Pellis who loves to look nice is actually from a cold region of Prius. Silva Pellis is very curious bestia and its coat is so unique that it can shakes off all the ice from its coat with one shake. He is known to be very adept with its paw (some rumors say he can pierce its own ear). Even though Silva looks very friendly and nice, he is especially ferocious in battle.

Rumor says Albior was one of its kind among his race. But he was secreted getting bullied by his own friends because of his unique looks. Albior was hurt both physically and mentally, and when he was about to give up, Anima reached out to him. As result, Albior began to love Xenor and anima.

In the Northern beach of a secret island, peaceful group of polar bears live. Acandus is a distant relative to these polar bears. Even though Acandus looks ferocious on the outside, he is actually very capable to read and write. More than anything, adventors love to hide in his belly to prevent conflicts with dangerous bestias.

Panthera possesses beautiful coat and fangs, which made her very popular among hunters. As result, he ended up distancing himself from adventors. However, anima reached out to remaining Panthera to offer her help, and Panthera finally started opening up to adventors. Even though he seems to not like adventors, he works hard to protect his master and anima.

As a descendent of Golden Wolf, Rehuka possesses unique charisma. She usually keeps to herself to hide her dog-like personality. Sometimes, when she see frisbee flying across her, she tries her best to repress her resire to chase after it.

Rumor says Albior was one of its kind among his race. But he was secreted getting bullied by his own friends because of his unique looks. Albior was hurt both physically and mentally, and when he was about to give up, Anima reached out to him. As result, Albior began to love Xenor and anima.
Nakra sometimes gets mistaken for a bestia, but he is actually a dragon that never grows in size. Nakra is known to love anima so much that he sometimes gets jealous of his own master.
Peakoko is famous for being full of herself. As result, she is well known for being not much help other than as a pet. She would always choose the safety of her own feather than own master.
Skuma is a very defensive bestia. He is always self-protecting, so he would choose not to fight in any situation if he had an option.

Sharp Ukorn possesses beautiful golden horn, but she is also infamous for being lazy. She would only do as much as she is fed. If she is hungry, she refuses to move. And also, when she sees imminent danger, you can always find her running away.

Donata is sometimes mistaken for being hot tempered because she always moves her wing. But in reality, she loves to observe things for a long time. Adventors often find her pondering with her big, beautiful eyes. Only downside of Donata would be that she moves her wings so fast and adventors sometimes throw up out of dizziness.

Who said snails are slow? Coclaura changed this sterotypical aspect of snail to 180 degrees. Coclaura is very diligent and fast pero. Also he loves to use his shell to protect Xenor and anima from danger. But he is always worried for eye infection when he travels fast.

Krisari possesses very beautiful wings. Since there are not too many insect peros, presence of Krisari itself draws a lot of attention. He hates being called 'giant moth.' So he would always remind anima that he is a butterfly, not a moth. But his effort is always in vain because Xenor could not possibly understand what he was trying to say.

During May, the month of children, one bright Hume inventor decided to make a cute pero just for animas. Unlike other peros, Popeti does not require taming. Even though this product targetted anima, it seems like Xenor might be more interested.

Rikano is loved by female adventors due to her exquisite way of walking. Rikano displays very noble appearance, and she also possesses the personality of nobility, which makes her very much favorable among female adventors.
Special edition of Celero technology which originated from Gigas technology. It might look faster because it is red, but its speed is exactly same as ordinary celero.

Who said turtles were slow? Quersi completely breaks the sterotypical aspect of turtle being slow. Althought Quersi seems gentle and calm, he has a bad habit of stomping everything on his path. But he possesses a very cool personality and forgets about master's mistake quick.

Evnia is a very shy pero who is considered to be extremely feminine by many adventors. Also unlike her giant appearance, she could actually be very young. She eats a lot and sleep a lot. Even though she might seem to move slow, she could actually be faster than normal pero due to her size. When she feels good, she moves her ears around. Many adventors find this very attractive.

Since Arak has a very poor eye sight, he recognizes his master by smell. If he does not recognize the smell, he assumes that it is an enemy. But he shows a lot of weakness in food, so many adventors tamed this bestia by luring with food.

Some rumors say Nigrata became a bestia under the curse of a nameless knight. Nigrata shows similar personality compared to the one of knights, so the rumors might be true for once. He is very gentle toward animas and women, and he shows no mercy to the enemies of his master.

Long time ago, a bright scholar poured his entire knowledge into one book. When he died, Regnus Adventists got the hold of the book. But luckily, the book was sealed with powerful magic that Regnust Adventists could not unseal. So Regnust Adventists decided to destroy this book to prevent it from being used by adventors. However, the book received so much magia from Adventists' effort to destroy it. As result, the book ended up gaining its own will and ability to move. Ever since than, Bukra became a pero to help out adventors.

A Beriah artisan who was in loved with one anima decided to build a wagon for the anima. This wagon resembled apple so much that he ended up naming it 'Pomone.' And a Latus gentleman who was also close with the anima offered to drive the wagon for her. Ever since than the descentent of Latus took pride in driving this wagon for the anima.

Humes used to research about the Gigas technology as well in order to create more effective pero. As a fruit of the research, Pysce was born. Even though Pysce is an ocean animal shaped, he has no problem traveling on land. Also, despite being a robot, anima and he seem to have a lot of connection between them. Nonetheless, since he is a robot, he sometimes does silly things.

Panpanda is a very lazy pero. Sometimes, he gets so lazy that he forgets to breathe. Knowing how Panpanda is, it is simply surprising to see a Panpanda giving rides to Xenor and anima. But rumors say it is due to Panpanda's personality. Panpanda likes to rank things that he does not want to do. Giving rides to Xenor and anima was simply not among the top 5 list.

Long time ago, a bright scholar poured his entire knowledge into one book. When he died, Regnus Adventists got the hold of the book. But luckily, the book was sealed with powerful magic that Regnust Adventists could not unseal. So Regnust Adventists decided to destroy this book to prevent it from being used by adventors. However, the book received so much magia from Adventists' effort to destroy it. As result, the book ended up gaining its own will and ability to move. Ever since than, Bukra became a pero to help out adventors.

A Beriah artisan who was in loved with one anima decided to build a wagon for the anima. This wagon resembled apple so much that he ended up naming it 'Pomone.' And a Latus gentleman who was also close with the anima offered to drive the wagon for her. Ever since than the descentent of Latus took pride in driving this wagon for the anima.

Humes used to research about the Gigas technology as well in order to create more effective pero. As a fruit of the research, Pysce was born. Even though Pysce is an ocean animal shaped, he has no problem traveling on land. Also, despite being a robot, anima and he seem to have a lot of connection between them. Nonetheless, since he is a robot, he sometimes does silly things.

Panpanda is a very lazy pero. Sometimes, he gets so lazy that he forgets to breathe. Knowing how Panpanda is, it is simply surprising to see a Panpanda giving rides to Xenor and anima. But rumors say it is due to Panpanda's personality. Panpanda likes to rank things that he does not want to do. Giving rides to Xenor and anima was simply not among the top 5 list.

Who said turtles were slow? Quersi completely breaks the sterotypical aspect of turtle being slow. Althought Quersi seems gentle and calm, he has a bad habit of stomping everything on his path. But he possesses a very cool personality and forgets about master's mistake quick.

Evnia is a very shy pero who is considered to be extremely feminine by many adventors. Also unlike her giant appearance, she could actually be very young. She eats a lot and sleep a lot. Even though she might seem to move slow, she could actually be faster than normal pero due to her size. When she feels good, she moves her ears around. Many adventors find this very attractive.

Rikano is loved by female adventors due to her exquisite way of walking. Rikano displays very noble appearance, and she also possesses the personality of nobility, which makes her very much favorable among female adventors.
Nakra sometimes gets mistaken for a bestia, but he is actually a dragon that never grows in size. Nakra is known to love anima so much that he sometimes gets jealous of his own master.
Peakoko is famous for being full of herself. As result, she is well known for being not much help other than as a pet. She would always choose the safety of her own feather than own master.
Skuma is a very defensive bestia. He is always self-protecting, so he would choose not to fight in any situation if he had an option.

Sharp Ukorn possesses beautiful golden horn, but she is also infamous for being lazy. She would only do as much as she is fed. If she is hungry, she refuses to move. And also, when she sees imminent danger, you can always find her running away.

Donata is sometimes mistaken for being hot tempered because she always moves her wing. But in reality, she loves to observe things for a long time. Adventors often find her pondering with her big, beautiful eyes. Only downside of Donata would be that she moves her wings so fast and adventors sometimes throw up out of dizziness.

Who said snails are slow? Coclaura changed this sterotypical aspect of snail to 180 degrees. Coclaura is very diligent and fast pero. Also he loves to use his shell to protect Xenor and anima from danger. But he is always worried for eye infection when he travels fast.

Krisari possesses very beautiful wings. Since there are not too many insect peros, presence of Krisari itself draws a lot of attention. He hates being called 'giant moth.' So he would always remind anima that he is a butterfly, not a moth. But his effort is always in vain because Xenor could not possibly understand what he was trying to say.

Rumor says Albior was one of its kind among his race. But he was secreted getting bullied by his own friends because of his unique looks. Albior was hurt both physically and mentally, and when he was about to give up, Anima reached out to him. As result, Albior began to love Xenor and anima.

In the Northern beach of a secret island, peaceful group of polar bears live. Acandus is a distant relative to these polar bears. Even though Acandus looks ferocious on the outside, he is actually very capable to read and write. More than anything, adventors love to hide in his belly to prevent conflicts with dangerous bestias.

Panthera possesses beautiful coat and fangs, which made her very popular among hunters. As result, he ended up distancing himself from adventors. However, anima reached out to remaining Panthera to offer her help, and Panthera finally started opening up to adventors. Even though he seems to not like adventors, he works hard to protect his master and anima.

As a descendent of Golden Wolf, Rehuka possesses unique charisma. She usually keeps to herself to hide her dog-like personality. Sometimes, when she see frisbee flying across her, she tries her best to repress her resire to chase after it.

Silva Pellis who loves to look nice is actually from a cold region of Prius. Silva Pellis is very curious bestia and its coat is so unique that it can shakes off all the ice from its coat with one shake. He is known to be very adept with its paw (some rumors say he can pierce its own ear). Even though Silva looks very friendly and nice, he is especially ferocious in battle.

Karabi has a unique look with its large body and horn, so many adventors make wrong assumption about Karabi. But he is actually a very peaceful bestia who gets along especially with Anima. Many adventors think that he looks gross by the way he walks, but he is also very popular to even have a backpack after him. He is especially popular among race manias.

Bicolen displays unique and noble looks that no peros can match. She was loved by Ayin in the past for her exquisite looks. Unlike some peros that refuse to move when hungry, Bicolen honors her master more than anything. She is a bestia that detests weakness, but she actually loves to eat plants.

This black lion is known to be the king of all peros. Also he is rumored to be the father of Jubata. Another rumor says scar on his eye was from the battle against Regnus Adventists. He is told to have become very ferocious because he lost his son during the battle. There are many rumors about Leogiti, but one thing for sure is that he can be trusted no matter what.

Moa is loved by many female adventors for her unique way of walking and exceptionally cool personality. Due to her unique personality, she never gets in trouble with adventors. But when she encounters an enemy, she will not hesitate to use her bodyslam and front kick.

Marino is an amphibious pero who is also very friendly to adventors. He likes exploring new areas and is known to be very curious. Even though he sometimes gets too curious, he is nonetheless very good to keep in company.

Rikano is loved by female adventors due to her exquisite way of walking. Rikano displays very noble appearance, and she also possesses the personality of nobility, which makes her very much favorable among female adventors.
Nakra sometimes gets mistaken for a bestia, but he is actually a dragon that never grows in size. Nakra is known to love anima so much that he sometimes gets jealous of his own master.
Peakoko is famous for being full of herself. As result, she is well known for being not much help other than as a pet. She would always choose the safety of her own feather than own master.
Skuma is a very defensive bestia. He is always self-protecting, so he would choose not to fight in any situation if he had an option.

Sharp Ukorn possesses beautiful golden horn, but she is also infamous for being lazy. She would only do as much as she is fed. If she is hungry, she refuses to move. And also, when she sees imminent danger, you can always find her running away.

Donata is sometimes mistaken for being hot tempered because she always moves her wing. But in reality, she loves to observe things for a long time. Adventors often find her pondering with her big, beautiful eyes. Only downside of Donata would be that she moves her wings so fast and adventors sometimes throw up out of dizziness.

Who said snails are slow? Coclaura changed this sterotypical aspect of snail to 180 degrees. Coclaura is very diligent and fast pero. Also he loves to use his shell to protect Xenor and anima from danger. But he is always worried for eye infection when he travels fast.

Krisari possesses very beautiful wings. Since there are not too many insect peros, presence of Krisari itself draws a lot of attention. He hates being called 'giant moth.' So he would always remind anima that he is a butterfly, not a moth. But his effort is always in vain because Xenor could not possibly understand what he was trying to say.

Rumor says Albior was one of its kind among his race. But he was secreted getting bullied by his own friends because of his unique looks. Albior was hurt both physically and mentally, and when he was about to give up, Anima reached out to him. As result, Albior began to love Xenor and anima.

In the Northern beach of a secret island, peaceful group of polar bears live. Acandus is a distant relative to these polar bears. Even though Acandus looks ferocious on the outside, he is actually very capable to read and write. More than anything, adventors love to hide in his belly to prevent conflicts with dangerous bestias.

Panthera possesses beautiful coat and fangs, which made her very popular among hunters. As result, he ended up distancing himself from adventors. However, anima reached out to remaining Panthera to offer her help, and Panthera finally started opening up to adventors. Even though he seems to not like adventors, he works hard to protect his master and anima.

As a descendent of Golden Wolf, Rehuka possesses unique charisma. She usually keeps to herself to hide her dog-like personality. Sometimes, when she see frisbee flying across her, she tries her best to repress her resire to chase after it.

Silva Pellis who loves to look nice is actually from a cold region of Prius. Silva Pellis is very curious bestia and its coat is so unique that it can shakes off all the ice from its coat with one shake. He is known to be very adept with its paw (some rumors say he can pierce its own ear). Even though Silva looks very friendly and nice, he is especially ferocious in battle.

Karabi has a unique look with its large body and horn, so many adventors make wrong assumption about Karabi. But he is actually a very peaceful bestia who gets along especially with Anima. Many adventors think that he looks gross by the way he walks, but he is also very popular to even have a backpack after him. He is especially popular among race manias.

Bicolen displays unique and noble looks that no peros can match. She was loved by Ayin in the past for her exquisite looks. Unlike some peros that refuse to move when hungry, Bicolen honors her master more than anything. She is a bestia that detests weakness, but she actually loves to eat plants.

This black lion is known to be the king of all peros. Also he is rumored to be the father of Jubata. Another rumor says scar on his eye was from the battle against Regnus Adventists. He is told to have become very ferocious because he lost his son during the battle. There are many rumors about Leogiti, but one thing for sure is that he can be trusted no matter what.

Moa is loved by many female adventors for her unique way of walking and exceptionally cool personality. Due to her unique personality, she never gets in trouble with adventors. But when she encounters an enemy, she will not hesitate to use her bodyslam and front kick.

Marino is an amphibious pero who is also very friendly to adventors. He likes exploring new areas and is known to be very curious. Even though he sometimes gets too curious, he is nonetheless very good to keep in company.

At first, Xenor was hesitant to use this bestia as pero due to its unusual appearance. But his effort to be close to Xenor and anima caught much attention, which became the turning point of Coelacanth to be loved as a pero. Unlike its dull face, Coelacanth laughs when he feels good. However, since there is no change in face expression, adventors sometimes get confused where the noise is coming from.

Family line of Sir Oscar goes way back in history. Due to their agile and brave aspect, they were trained to be guard dogs for adventors. But a unique genetic mutation started happening, which caused some of them to grow extremely big. Ever since then, adventors started training them as peros. Since they are extremely smart and agile, they sometimes ignore adventors, but they are loyal nonetheless. Also they are very fashionable in the way they dress.

Aries is popular among adventors due to her cute face and body. But despite her bright personality, she has some painful past. Long time ago, adventors used to travel to high plateau to hunt Aries for the wool and meat. As result, Aries had to always be careful of adventors. Nonetheless, she found Xenor and anima who took care of Aries when her life was in danger. Ever since then, she decided to serve them as masters. She received a present from anima, which was a mount and a bell. The bell is her favorite accessory.

She received a present from anima, which was a mount and a bell. The bell is her favorite accessory.

Aufero is a carnivorous bird who is very ferocious and stubborn. He is very capable to travel long distance very fast, but he does not like doing favors for Xenor. When he encounters something he does not like, he will not hesitate to use his claws. But once tamed, he never betrays his master.
Berdes was specially bred and picked for Foederis Chief Officer of Parangkes. He displays unique and noble looks, and he is also very loyal to his master.
Fululos was specially bred and picked for Foederis officers of Parangkes. Fululos might look simple, but he is nonetheless one of most loyal pero anyone could find.

Along with Berdes, Glacus is specially picked for Himes Chief Officer of Parangkes. This pero will always keep his temper low and stay calm at all time. But he is not exactly the friendliest pero, and he is infamous to only serve those he chooses.
Along with Fululos, Alcius is picked for Himes officers of Parangkes. This pero might look simple, but its stamina is incomparable to other peros.

Fogsteed was created by evil energy and fog. Since fog is a part of nature's work, Fogsteed possesses the personality of a little kid. He listens to anima well, but he also seems to be missing something.

Nightmare received his name from his looks when he runs in the dark. Many adventors are scared to meet Nightmare at first because of his appearance. However, once tamed, Nightmare is very friendly and obeys his master extremely well. One thing for sure is that masters need to be sure to unsummon Nightmare before they go to sleep.

Equifox has 8 legs and emits flame from his body. Because he is always active, he pants whenever he is standing still. Equifox, unlike its appearance, is a very patient and calm pero, which is quite the opposite of Equinix.

Equinix has 8 legs and emits cold aura from his body. Because he is always active, he pants whenever he is standing still. Equinix, unlike its appearance, is not much of a  thinker. He sometimes blanks out and trip over his own leg, which is quite the opposite of Equipox.

Windlandir can only be seen during certain season. She was born with special magia, which gave her red noise and a ribbon at the tip of her tail. In order to celebrate Christmas, her birthday, she wears pretty lace around her neck.

Nejutia can only be seen during certain season. Unlike Kornoir and Winglandir, she has a unique background. Originally, Silva Pellis used to love decorating themselves. Among those, one Silva Pellis love Christmas so much that he wore Santa hat everyday. As result, he was known as Nejutia instead.

Repus can only be seen during certain season. Special magia energy allows rabbits to lead the sled (but it is not particularly fast on snow). If you miss the opportunity, you will have to wait a year for it.

But if an adventor shows any sigh of weakness, he will take his chance and run away. Because Jubata is fast and costs very little to maintain, he is very popular among the adventors

Ensis seems ferocious on the outside, but he is more gentle bestia than a unicorn. Ensis is well known to be a gentle bestia to both enemies and allies, but he is also well known to kill his prey instantly to minimize their pain. Unlike other felines, Ensis does not play around with his prey.

This pero displays a unique look of Eastern dragon. Duan Boats were designed by an artisan from the east, and a rumor tells that he made this pero as a tribute to an important holiday of the east. This pero gained special power from the soul of the artisan, which allowed it to understand the feelings of Xenor and anima.
King Leoberita of all bestia. There is little known about this bestia. This bestia controls what goes on in the Vine Maze.
Cornix is a ferocious black bird that has black diamonds instead his own eyes. This bestia will attack its enemy with unique noise, and this noise can only be controlled by a special bell.
The legs of Spotted Sole Bear were mutated by Red Bee's magia. Despite its appearance, he is known to be quite gentle. Due to his mutation, he is being hunted down by many scientists as test subject.
Snowstorm Owl is only found in cold northern region. Unlike ordinary owls, Snowstorm owls also stay active during the day. They do not reside in one place for a long time.

Lake Rhinoceros is a unique bestia only found in Lake Garden. Unlike its gentle appearance, he is very quite ferocious with his horn. He always stay near the water. Absence of water or presence of defiled water makes Lake Rhinoceros extremely weak.

Panpanda is a very lazy pero. Sometimes, he gets so lazy that he forgets to breathe. Knowing how Panpanda is, it is simply surprising to see a Panpanda giving rides to Xenor and anima. But rumors say it is due to Panpanda's personality. Panpanda likes to rank things that he does not want to do. Giving rides to Xenor and anima was simply not among the top 5 list.

Xenor and Anima were in pursuit of finding a new pero to celebrate the new year. Then one day, they discover an oversized chicken and a chick. This mount features top tier technology that took Humes many years to perfect. As a modified version of celero technology, Santa's Snowmobile is equipped with 250cc Magia engine. Its design has been perfected by a team of talented artisans, and color and overall display features spirit of Christmas. Before Santa's Snowmobile went into production, Admiral Lachel from Aurora yelled, "What were you guys thinking? Spending city budget on a pero production? Nonsense!" But after glancing through the catalog, Admiral Lachel changed her mind and put in an early order with a comment, "It's about time I get a new pero."
